On interrupt, the state of registers is saved in the current task stack.

Before interrupt:		After saving registers:

        | ///////////// |               | ///////////// |
	|---------------|               |---------------|
  ESP-> | ///////////// |     Old ESP ->| ///////////// |
	|---------------|               |---------------|
	|               |               |     EFLAGS    |
	|---------------|               |---------------|
	|               |               |      CS       |
	|---------------|               |---------------|
	|               |               |      EIP      |
	|---------------|               |---------------|
	|               |               |      ERR *    | saved by 386 hardware
	|---------------|               |---------------|
	|               |               |      EAX      |       pushal
	|---------------|               |---------------|
	|               |               |      ECX      |
        |---------------|               |---------------|
        |               |               |      EDX      |
                                        |---------------|
                                        |      EBX      |
                                        |---------------|
                                        |      ESP      |
                                        |---------------|
                                        |      EBP      |
                                        |---------------|
                                        |      ESI      |
                                        |---------------|
                                        |      EDI      |
                                        |---------------|
                                        |      DS       |       SEG_SAVE
                                        |---------------|
                               New SP ->|      ES       |
                                        |---------------|
                                        |               |


			    
